{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2021/10/15/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"EbookFoundation/free-programming-books","categoryHTML":"<h3>Windows Phone</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20150709045622/http://download.microsoft.com/download/C/4/6/C4635738-5E06-4DF7-904E-BDC22AED2E58/Developing%20an%20Advanced%20Windows%20Phone%207.5%20App%20that%20Connects%20to%20the%20Cloud.pdf\">Developing An Advanced Windows Phone 7.5 App That Connects To The Cloud</a> - MSDN Library, David Britch, Francis Cheung, Adam Kinney, Rohit Sharma (PDF) (🗃️ <em>archived</em>)</li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T23:39:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"EbookFoundation/free-programming-books","categoryHTML":"<h3>NoSQL</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://redis.com/ebook/redis-in-action/\">Redis in Action</a> - Josiah L. Carlson</li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T23:35:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sdras/awesome-actions","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community Resources</h2><h3>Fun</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ariary/Readme-Like-Button\">Add equivalent of a like button in your README</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ariary/Readme-Like-Button\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1,\"repo\":\"ariary/Readme-Like-Button\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Visualize community approval on some part of your readme (can be used as a poll).</li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T22:29:26.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"edm00se/awesome-board-games","categoryHTML":"<h2>Family</h2>","itemHTML":"<h3><a href=\"https://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/204583/kingdomino\">Kingdomino</a></h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In Kingdomino, you are playing as a lord who is seeking new lands to expand your kingdom. You must explore all the lands, including wheat fields, lakes, and mountains, to spot the best plots, while competing with other lords to acquire them first. This game is like Dominoes. It uses tiles with two sections. Each turn, player will select a new domino to connect to their existing kingdom, making sure at least one of its sides connects to a matching terrain type already in play. The order of who picks first depends on which tile was previously chosen, with better tiles forcing players to pick later in the next round. The game ends when each player has completed a 5x5 grid and then points are counted based on number of connecting tiles and crowns symbol.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"https://cf.geekdo-images.com/3h9W8BfB_rltQ48EBmHliw__itemrep/img/iL7bbm8d4meLUnnrFrmKx0Xk2k0=/fit-in/246x300/filters:strip_icc()/pic3132685.png\" alt=\"Kingdomino image\"></p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th align=\"right\">Players</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Min. Age</th>\n<th align=\"right\">Time</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"right\">2 - 4</td>\n<td align=\"right\">8</td>\n<td align=\"right\">15m</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T19:12:46.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ripienaar/free-for-dev","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools for Teams and Collaboration</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://fleep.io/\">Fleep.io</a> — Fleep an alternative to Slack. It has a free plan for small teams with full message history, unlimited 1:1 conversations, 1 group conversation and 1 GB file storage.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T19:00:12.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"ripienaar/free-for-dev","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools for Teams and Collaboration</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://chanty.com/\">Chanty.com</a> — Chanty is another alternative to Slack. It has a free forever plan for small teams (up to 10) with unlimited public and private conversations, searchable history, unlimited 1:1 audio calls, unlimited voice messages, 10 integrations and 20 GB storage per team.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T19:00:12.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aliesbelik/awesome-jmeter","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tutorials</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://datacadamia.com/jmeter/lifecycle\">JMeter: Load Development Lifecycle</a> - By DataCadamia.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T15:42:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aliesbelik/awesome-jmeter","categoryHTML":"<h2>Cloud Services / SaaS</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://octoperf.com/\">OctoPerf</a> - SaaS and On-Premise Load Testing Tool with JMeter and Selenium support.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T15:42:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aliesbelik/awesome-jmeter","categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2><h3>Extending JMeter</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20180225144718/http://artur.ejsmont.org/blog/content/how-to-build-a-jmeter-plugin-utilising-groovy\">How to build a JMeter plugin utilizing Groovy</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T15:42:55.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://scythe-studio.com/blog\">Scythe-Studio</a> - Yet another consulting company specialized in Qt\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://scythe-studio.com/blog/qt-creator-cheat-sheet\">Qt Creator Cheat Sheet</a> - Convenient document for improving your familiarity with Qt Creator IDE.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://scythe-studio.com/blog/deploying-app-and-generating-offline-installers-for-windows-qt-installer-framework-tutorial\">Qt Installer Framework tutorial</a> - Series about practical usage of Qt Installer framework with in-depth overview of different features.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://scythe-studio.com/blog/how-to-interface-qt-with-android-java-code\">How to interface Qt with Android Java code</a> - Getting wild and \"native\" with Android code in your Qt application.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://scythe-studio.com/blog/nfc-in-qt-qml-application\">How to use NFC in Qt/Qml application?</a> - Have you ever wondered how to use NFC in Qt/Qml application? This blog post will give you a complex overview of the concept of near-field communication technology with examples of its usage in real life.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T15:27:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.qt.io/product/qt6/qml-book\">Qt6 QML Book</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/qmlbook/qt6book\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/qmlbook/qt6book\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">205</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":205,\"repo\":\"qmlbook/qt6book\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->, by Johan Thelin, Jürgen Bocklage-Ryannel and Cyril Lorquet - Free book created by Qt Company. It provides you with a walk through of the different aspects of application development using the new Qt 6. It focuses on the Qt Quick technology, but also provides necessary information about writing C++ back-ends and extension for Qt Quick.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-10-15T15:27:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software that Uses Qt</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a